{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "03", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "18", "S": "58"}}, "news": [{"title": "Register Lucknow development body's properties at special camp from Nov 3-15", "para": "Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is organizing a 13-day 'single-window' camp from November 3-15 to expedite pending property registrations.  LDA officials will prepare documents for the first 10 days, with the registry department finalizing registrations on-site during the last three days. Allottees who have paid in full or 80% or more are being contacted to complete their property registries.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/special-camp-for-lucknow-development-authority-property-registration-from-nov-3-15/125046512?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39394/125046512.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Maharashtra moves to make redevelopment projects more viable", "para": "In an effort to revitalize Mumbai, the Maharashtra government is initiating a series of amendments to the city's development regulations. This overhaul is designed to support MHADA in streamlining housing redevelopment projects, ultimately enhancing financial feasibility for builders. The proposal also includes extended benefits for tenants to ensure smooth rehousing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtra-government-proposes-changes-to-boost-redevelopment-viability-in-mumbai/125046479?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-107280/125046479.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "PNB Housing Finance shortlists four for MD & CEO position", "para": "PNB Housing Finance is close to appointing a new Managing Director and CEO. Four candidates have been shortlisted, with Ajai S